1
00:00:10,416 --> 00:00:15,083
♪

2
00:02:19,083 --> 00:02:20,375
[KALININ]
The damage will be much worse

3
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:22,041
if those units reach land.

4
00:02:22,125 --> 00:02:24,166
[TESSA] What's the
status of our AS team?

5
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:26,000
[KALININ]
They're standing by.

6
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:29,666
[TESSA] Very well.
Squad Captain Urzu One.

7
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,750
You may launch your
attack when ready.

8
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,083
[CLOUSEAU]
Yes ma'am.

9
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:38,875
[CLOUSEAU] Urzu One to
all units. Here's the plan.

10
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:41,625
Urzu Three, Five,
Six, and Eight,

11
00:02:41,708 --> 00:02:43,583
you'll take down Behemoth B.

12
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:45,458
[KURZ]
What about the other two?

13
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:48,458
[CLOUSEAU] Urzu Two and I
will keep them occupied.

14
00:02:48,541 --> 00:02:52,916
I'll engage Behemoth C. And Urzu
Two will take Behemoth A.

15
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,833
Lieutenant. You got that?

16
00:02:54,916 --> 00:02:56,458
[MAO]
Urzu Two, I copy.

17
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:59,000
I'll rough him up
as much as I can.

18
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,541
[CLOUSEAU]
You don't need to win.

19
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:03,125
Just buy us some time while Kurz
and the others take down B.

20
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:04,666
They better not screw it up.

21
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:05,833
[alarm beeps]

22
00:03:05,916 --> 00:03:07,625
[MAO]
Behemoth A is now in range.

23
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:10,416
[CLOUSEAU] You're clear
to use ITCC Arm Slaves.

24
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:14,250
Urzu Two. Roger that.
Time to rock.

25
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:51,083
[MAO]
All right. First we say hello.

26
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,416
[MAO]
And to follow up.

27
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,958
[MAO]
No damage.

28
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:30,833
Your Lambda driver might
block normal attacks,

29
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:34,250
but you can't block what you
don't see coming, now can you?

30
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:42,458
[MAO]
There we go.

31
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:45,500
[MAO]
This is Urzu Two.

32
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:47,833
It wasn't much,
but I damaged the target.

33
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:48,791
This is gonna work!

34
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:50,083
[KALININ]
This is Perth One.

35
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,291
We have inbound
enemy helicopters.

36
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:55,166
They're likely transporting
ground forces.

37
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:57,333
We need you to neutralize
those behemoths

38
00:04:57,416 --> 00:05:01,125
before they're reinforced.
Otherwise, we're finished.

39
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:06,791
"Neutralize." He makes
it sound so simple.

40
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,791
--[alarm beeps]
--[MAO gasps]

41
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:35,291
This is Urzu Two. Behemoth A
just returned fire.

42
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:38,208
I'll continue harassing it
once I've changed positions.

43
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:40,416
Careful Mao. Don't die.

44
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:44,916
[SPECK] Urzu Eight to Urzu Six.
What's wrong, kid? You scared?

45
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,583
[KURZ chuckles]
No way, I'm pumped.

46
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,458
[SPECK] Don't forget that
you're in charge of this part

47
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:50,625
of the mission.

48
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:52,375
We'll be out there
pokin' the bull for ya,

49
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:54,166
so keep your head
in the game, yeah?

50
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,375
[KURZ]
I hear ya.

51
00:05:55,458 --> 00:05:59,000
[SPECK]
Hm... By the way, Kurz.

52
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,500
[KURZ]
What's up?

53
00:06:00,583 --> 00:06:03,041
D'ya think Tessa
would've actually...?

54
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:08,583
Nah. Forget it.
Doesn't matter anyway.

55
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:14,375
[KURZ] She wasn't gonna
shoot you. The captain? No way.

56
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:15,791
[SPECK]
Right.

57
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:18,166
Now. If it was me,
I'd'a taken the shot.

58
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,916
[SPECK]
Ha! You punk.

59
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,750
It's time we got to it.
Ready, Urzu Eight?

60
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,375
I was born ready!

61
00:06:24,458 --> 00:06:25,541
[KURZ]
Urzu Five?

62
00:06:25,625 --> 00:06:27,208
I'm with you, Urzu Six.

63
00:06:27,291 --> 00:06:28,500
[KURZ]
Urzu Three!

64
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,125
Just give the word, Sergeant.

65
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,041
All right. Let's give 'em hell!

66
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,583
[FEMALE AI A]
Fairy Eye is now active.

67
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,750
[KURZ]
This thing's useful.

68
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,333
Looks like they started
guarding against our

69
00:06:42,416 --> 00:06:45,083
self-propelled naval mines.

70
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:47,041
[CLOUSEAU] So the Lambda
driver can defend against

71
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:49,041
any conventional weapon.

72
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:50,708
And you're certain
that's the case?

73
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:52,041
[LEMMING]
Yes.

74
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:54,208
However, the Lambda driver
is reliant on its user.

75
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:57,041
It can only form a field against
threats the pilot knows of.

76
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,750
So we just need
to surprise them.

77
00:06:58,833 --> 00:06:59,541
[LEMMING]
Yes.

78
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:00,875
All right. But wait.

79
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:03,000
What should we target?
Where's the cockpit?

80
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:04,541
[LEMMING]
The head.

81
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:07,791
That said. Don't expect to bring
one down with a single shot.

82
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,250
Correct.

83
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:11,541
As things stand, even if you
bypass the Lambda driver,

84
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:14,625
the M9's weaponry won't
pierce that composite armor.

85
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:15,750
We can't hurt 'em?

86
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,041
Not with one shot.

87
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:19,875
But hit the same point twice,
in the head,

88
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,958
and using 76 millimeter rounds,

89
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,791
there's a good chance that
we could bring one down.

90
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:26,791
[LEMMING]
That would likely work.

91
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:28,625
[CLOUSEAU]
All right. We surprise them,

92
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:29,708
misdirect their focus,

93
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:32,041
and strike their
weakest point. The head.

94
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:34,041
We get one chance
to pull this off.

95
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:36,583
Once their guard's up,
it's over.

96
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,000
[CASTELLO]
Hm.

97
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:41,208
Yeah, that's insane. We don't
have a chance in hell.

98
00:07:41,291 --> 00:07:44,166
This almost makes me
wanna surrender again.

99
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:45,625
[KURZ]
Huh, ya know what?

100
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:46,791
[SPECK]
Hm?

101
00:07:46,875 --> 00:07:49,750
Yeah. Crazy or not,
it might just work.

102
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,333
[MAO]
You have an idea?

103
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:53,666
[KURZ chuckles]
All right.

104
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:56,958
This shouldn't be any harder
than threading a needle.

105
00:07:57,041 --> 00:07:58,666
You know the plan.

106
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:01,708
First, we'll hit 'em with a
triple feint. Counting down.

107
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:05,083
[KURZ]
From three... two... one!

108
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,916
Alpha. Go!

109
00:08:42,791 --> 00:08:44,375
[KURZ]
Beta. Go!

110
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:49,833
[gasps]

111
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:00,500
Take this!

112
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:16,125
[SPECK shouts]

113
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:20,166
[KURZ]
Good. He's all over the place.

114
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:22,958
[KURZ] Go.

115
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:25,125
Urzu 3. Roger that.

116
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:50,166
[KURZ gasps]

117
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,041
[KURZ grunts]

118
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,916
[KURZ]
Shit! I screwed up.

119
00:10:12,125 --> 00:10:14,000
[KURZ]
We have to take cover!

120
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,708
[CASTELLO]
Yeah, ya don't say.

121
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:24,875
[THUNDERRAPTOR grunts]
He got me.

122
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:25,916
[alarm beeps]

123
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,583
Nothing we can do now.

124
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,583
[KURZ]
Looks like we're finished.

125
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:32,541
[SPECK]
Not yet!

126
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:33,791
[KURZ]
Speck?

127
00:10:33,875 --> 00:10:35,291
[SPECK]
Line up your next shot.

128
00:10:35,375 --> 00:10:38,166
I'll get you one
more chance, okay?

129
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,458
One more!

130
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:52,208
[SPECK] This kind of thing isn't
really my style, but screw it.

131
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:57,083
[KURZ]
Let it go. Retreat!

132
00:10:57,166 --> 00:11:01,000
[SPECK] I need you to tell the
captain something. All right?

133
00:11:08,166 --> 00:11:11,166
[SPECK grunts]
What the--? Damn it!

134
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:13,291
[SPECK shouts]

135
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:22,083
[SPECK] Tell her that I
wouldn't've sold her out.

136
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:24,916
I don't want that to be
how she remembers me.

137
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:32,041
[gasps, screams]

138
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:34,000
[KURZ]
Speck!

139
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:39,250
Bastard!

140
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,375
Burn in hell.

141
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:20,750
[grunts]
Damn it, Speck... You idiot.

142
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:55,791
That oughtta slow
down your progress.

143
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:59,833
[KURZ] This is Urzu Six.
We defeated Behemoth B,

144
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:01,708
but Urzu 8 is dead.

145
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:14,500
[MAO] Urzu Two, out of ammo.
Just had to toss my rifle.

146
00:13:14,583 --> 00:13:16,458
[KURZ]
Mao! Check your radar!

147
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:17,875
[CLOUSEAU]
Urzu Two!

148
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:19,041
[KURZ]
Mao!

149
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:23,625
[MAO] I'm fine,
still have my shotcannon.

150
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:28,750
I think I can buy you
guys a little more time,

151
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,458
so focus on Behemoth C.

152
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:31,666
--[alarm beeps]
--[gasps]

153
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,166
You okay?!

154
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:38,000
[FEMALE AI A] Enemy air
units in sector S-Two.

155
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:40,291
Bearing two-oh-four.

156
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:43,000
[KURZ] Looks like our
guests showed up early.

157
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:35,791
[MAO grunts]

158
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,708
Urzu Two to all units.
I've taken damage.

159
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,583
Can anyone hear this?

160
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:51,708
So, this is the end. Shit.

161
00:15:02,291 --> 00:15:04,250
[CASTELLO]
Urzu Two! You still kickin'?

162
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:06,291
Lieutenant Castello!
Leave me! Get ou--

163
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:08,750
Not happening! Shut up and let--

164
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,250
[CASTELLO grunts]

165
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,541
[MAO]
Lieutenant!

166
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:17,500
[CASTELLO grunts, shouts]

167
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:18,916
[MAO]
No, wait!

168
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:24,500
[CASTELLO] I'll act as a decoy.
Abandon your mech and run!

169
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:26,000
Don't do this!

170
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:29,041
[CASTELLO] That's an order,
Second Lieutenant. Go!

171
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:37,375
[CASTELLO grunts]
Come get some, bastard!

172
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:38,958
[MAO grunts]

173
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,625
Castello, look out!

174
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,333
[CASTELLO shouts]

175
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:00,916
[MAO gasps]

176
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,125
[SHINOHARA]
Urzu Five is badly damaged.

177
00:16:31,208 --> 00:16:33,333
Pilot is injured, but stable.

178
00:16:33,416 --> 00:16:36,541
[MALE STAFF D] PRT Unit Two has
taken casualties. Three dead.

179
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:37,875
Eight critically injured!

180
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:39,083
[MALE AIR GUARD A]
Gebo Seven is non-responsive...

181
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,250
[KALININ] Enemy ground
forces have landed.

182
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,708
We're fighting tooth and nail,

183
00:16:42,791 --> 00:16:45,291
but I doubt we'll hold out
more than half an hour.

184
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:48,958
[TESSA] But the Danaan won't be
ready to set out for two hours.

185
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:52,750
[KALININ] I realize that.
But 30 minutes is what we have.

186
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,541
[TESSA]
In that case...

187
00:16:58,541 --> 00:16:59,708
[MARDUKAS]
This is Mardukas.

188
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:02,041
[TESSA]
Suspend reactor replenishment,

189
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:04,208
and allocate all spare
personnel to perform

190
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,291
a water tightness inspection.

191
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:09,250
Yes, Ma'am. I thought that
it might come to this.

192
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,625
We'll get it done.

193
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:12,000
But Madame Captain...

194
00:17:12,083 --> 00:17:13,958
Even if we can
escape this island,

195
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:16,625
we'll most likely be dead in
the water within two weeks.

196
00:17:16,708 --> 00:17:19,875
However, we have
no safe alternative.

197
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,166
Ma'am.

198
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:22,500
[TESSA gasps]

199
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:25,750
Kalinin.

200
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:26,958
[phone rings]

201
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:29,750
[SHINOHARA]
Captain! Urzu Six is calling in.

202
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,416
[TESSA]
Put him through.

203
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,000
[KURZ]
This is Urzu Six.

204
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:35,625
I'm currently in combat
with Behemoth A.

205
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:37,541
Doubt I'll be
able to destroy it.

206
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:40,000
But I have made it
waste a lot of ammo.

207
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:42,583
First Lieutenant
Castello was killed.

208
00:17:42,666 --> 00:17:44,500
I'm not sure about Mao.

209
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:47,833
Understood. Return to base ASAP.

210
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:50,958
I can't. You've got more
choppers inbound.

211
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:53,291
I'm gonna try and slow
them down a bit.

212
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:56,916
Urzu Six. You must be all-but
out of ammo, so fall back!

213
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,083
Kurz, that's an order!
You can't do this!

214
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:03,708
[KURZ] Hmph. Sorry, but my
hands are tied.

215
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,541
After the heroics
those guys pulled.

216
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:12,333
[KALININ]
Urzu Six, respond! Urzu Six!

217
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:13,666
Can you hear me?

218
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:15,666
[KURZ]
Well, here goes nothin'.

219
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:19,958
[MALE PA] Attention. Attention.
This is an emergency alert.

220
00:18:20,041 --> 00:18:23,708
Stay indoors if possible.
This is not a drill.

221
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:26,291
[SHINJI] They think it was
some kind of attack?

222
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:29,208
I can't believe they
stuck us in study hall.

223
00:18:29,291 --> 00:18:32,333
While the teachers are all
having an emergency meeting.

224
00:18:32,416 --> 00:18:35,041
If there was a terror attack
they should send us home.

225
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:39,166
This sucks. Makes me wish I'd
just cut class today. Ya know?

226
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,458
Speaking of skipping,

227
00:18:40,541 --> 00:18:43,208
I haven't seen Sousuke
or Chidori at all today.

228
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:44,916
I sure do hope it's not related.

229
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,041
Dunno. But Kyoko hasn't
shown up either.

230
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:49,458
Did you try calling her?

231
00:18:49,541 --> 00:18:53,125
[ONO-D] Yeah, but she
didn't answer! It's annoying.

232
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:55,625
I was just tryin' to
see what she's up to.

233
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:56,875
[sirens blaring]

234
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,500
[KYOKO whimpers]

235
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:00,708
[KURAMA]
You seem like a nice kid.

236
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:03,875
I want you to know that
none of this is your fault.

237
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:05,208
[KYOKO ehimpers]

238
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:08,000
To be honest, I feel a
little guilty about it,

239
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:10,958
but it's necessary for my job.

240
00:19:11,041 --> 00:19:13,291
You do know what that is, right?

241
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:14,875
[KYOKO whimpers]
Mm-hm.

242
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:17,333
[KURAMA]
Yeah. It's a bomb.

243
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:20,041
Here and there,
around your school,

244
00:19:20,125 --> 00:19:21,750
there are others just like it.

245
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:25,458
So if you make too much of
a fuss, or try to call for help,

246
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:28,083
it won't just be you
that gets killed.

247
00:19:28,166 --> 00:19:31,666
But if you behave yourself,
then no one has to die.

248
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:34,041
[phone rings]

249
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:36,791
[KYOKO gasps]

250
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,458
[KURAMA]
Well?

251
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:40,250
[HENCHMAN A] We've lost
sight of the target, sir.

252
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,541
But we're monitoring police
radio and telephone lines.

253
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,541
[KURAMA]
Just keep watching for him.

254
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:47,208
He knows that his
friends are in danger,

255
00:19:47,291 --> 00:19:49,500
so he's not about to run.

256
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:51,416
He's one of those hero types.

257
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,625
[MALE PA] We apologize
for the inconvenience.

258
00:19:53,708 --> 00:19:56,208
But due to the large-scale
communications disruptions

259
00:19:56,291 --> 00:19:58,791
that began this morning,
we're setting up checkpoints

260
00:19:58,875 --> 00:20:01,166
throughout the city as
a security precaution.

261
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,833
[MALE OFFICERS gasp]

262
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:25,500
[KANAME]
Mm?

263
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:38,625
[KANAME] The truth is.
I saw this coming.

264
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:43,083
I knew the life I've lived up
to now, couldn't last forever.

265
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:47,083
I knew that someday the enemy
would come to tear it all apart.

266
00:20:47,166 --> 00:20:48,583
I've been expecting this.

267
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:52,250
Bracing myself for
more than six months.

268
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,208
[SOUSUKE]
This isn't your fault.

269
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:56,916
[KANAME]
I'm scared.

270
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Of them... and of
my own mind, too.

271
00:21:01,083 --> 00:21:03,458
It keeps filling up with
all this information

272
00:21:03,541 --> 00:21:05,333
that I shouldn't know.

273
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:11,166
Sometimes, it feels as if I'm
turning into someone else.

274
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,416
Chidori...

275
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:16,791
[KANAME] Sorry, but you
scare me too, Sousuke.

276
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:20,666
Did you know that?
You terrify me.

277
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:23,458
So why is it that I
like you so much?

278
00:21:23,541 --> 00:21:26,166
It's dumb, but I feel both ways.

279
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:29,791
[sobs]

280
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:31,000
[SOUSUKE]
Same here.

281
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:33,750
[KANAME gasps]
Huh?

282
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:37,875
I can't help but like you,
yet... you scare me.

283
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:39,458
It's perplexing.

284
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:42,541
I don't understand you,
and yet I'm drawn to you.

285
00:21:42,625 --> 00:21:45,083
It's a cycle of
conflicting thoughts.

286
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:47,500
My whole world was
changed when I met you.

287
00:21:47,583 --> 00:21:49,333
And I'm glad.

288
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:51,041
Sousuke, I...

289
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:53,250
[SOUSUKE] We could run
away from all this.

290
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,500
But it won't feel right
if it's just us.

291
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:57,666
You won't be that student
council girl who jokes

292
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,750
with her friends and yells
at me for missing class.

293
00:22:02,125 --> 00:22:04,166
And that's how I need you.

294
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,625
That's why I'm going
to protect it all.

295
00:22:09,708 --> 00:22:11,250
I'll defend your whole world.

296
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,875
Every last thing that's
connected to you.

297
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:16,166
Do you think you can do that?

298
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,541
[SOUSUKE]
Probably not by myself.

299
00:22:18,625 --> 00:22:22,916
So I'd like you to help me.
Let's save our friends together.

300
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:27,833
I'm so scared.

301
00:22:27,916 --> 00:22:30,375
I am too. Very.

302
00:22:31,666 --> 00:22:35,000
[KANAME sighs]

303
00:22:35,083 --> 00:22:38,541
I'm with you.
Let's think up a plan.

304
00:22:38,625 --> 00:22:40,583
[KANAME chuckles]

305
00:22:40,666 --> 00:22:42,166
Thanks, Chidori.

306
00:22:47,291 --> 00:22:48,250
[KANAME chuckles]

307
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:53,291
♪

308
00:24:16,041 --> 00:24:18,333
[SOUSUKE]
Next time: "On My Own."

